 back alcove area where the bookstand is.  There is a pretty good chance of a see-hidden MOB or two being in the area so you'll want to proceed with caution and have that potion hotkeyed.  With luck, it's grab and go, without you may want to log out in the SW corner (harder to get to and back), the fountain (safeish) or upstairs by the nightstand itself (dangerous but handy if the book is there on your return).  If MOBs are cooperative, you might even just stay logged in and go do some housework or whatever else you have been neglecting lately.<br><br>It's fun and with an instant-cast potion, actually almost as safe as it gets.  Relying on a casted gate (or the Worker's Sledgehammer as one fellow once suggested) is, umm, more dangerous.  Certainly it can be done with a standard gate but have plans for CR if you choose this route.  Remember Murphy's law after all.  One final note though, even an instant gate won't save your Roguish hide from multiple Harmtouches or a well received stun.  Keep your eyes and ears open and your finger on the button.  Have fun now =)<br><br>cheers,<br>Celeris <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utrewayn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trewayn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/16/02 1:53:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3811.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the spoiler for acquiring Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> Regrding this, I'm trying to find the program which wasrefered to which allows you to train yourself on the zones. I believe it starts up a stand-alone version of EQ loaded with a pre-selected, unpopulated map which allows you to roam around the area and learn the lay of the land.  Does anyone have any information about this proggy, like where to get it etc? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulemacdushae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lemac Dushae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/16/02 4:30:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3811.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the spoiler for acquiring Book of Souls solo?</span><hr size=1> <br>It's called zone explorer.  You can get it at www.everlore.com once you do some searching. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3769.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3440.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3811.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3811.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3811.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3811.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive e